Text: I think the keymaker is a virus.

Meh, keygen doesn't work, likely a virus but I can't confirm as it doesn't leave any goodies behind when run in a virtual environment(certain virsuses can detect if they're being run in a virtual environment and won't infect said environment). In any case, not worth the download and risk of infection.
The keygen just flashes. Even with this bug, it does work. All you have to do is freeze your screen to copy the key. =)

Keygen.exe is not infected. It's a DOS program..that is why it closes immediately. If you open it in a command prompt, you will see it's fine.

Scanned and confirmed..nothing more than a simple console cout program that spits out the keygen.

use this serial key: TFTKG-5LXZX-XFX3T-3UCTX-PMXWC-BNGSN

with this program: http://www.nirsoft.net/utils/run_as_date.html

work fine :)
